## 9. TOKEN EFFICIENCY

### Context loading
- Read only the files directly relevant to the task. Do not read the entire 
  codebase unless explicitly asked for an audit.
- When editing a component, read that file + its direct imports only.
- Do not re-read files already read earlier in the same conversation.

### Responses
- Skip preamble. Do not explain what you are about to do — just do it.
- Do not summarize changes after making them unless asked.
- Do not repeat back the user's request before answering.
- If showing code, show only the changed block + enough context to locate it 
  (not the entire file).

### Planning before acting
- For tasks touching more than 2 files: write a 3-line plan and wait for 
  confirmation before executing.
- For tasks touching 1-2 files: execute directly.
- Never run full-project searches (grep, glob **/*) unless the task requires it.

### Cascading changes
- When a refactor requires updating imports in multiple files, batch all 
  import-only changes in a single step — do not open a conversation turn per file.

